00:10.100 --> 00:15.720
solely on sample information a specific value is called an estimate.

00:16.540 --> 00:23.990
There are two types of estimates point estimates and confidence interval estimates of point estimate

00:24.080 --> 00:25.380
is a single number.

00:25.430 --> 00:32.050
While a confidence interval naturally is an interval the two are closely related.

00:32.060 --> 00:37.880
In fact the point estimate is located exactly in the middle of the confidence interval.

00:37.950 --> 00:44.360
However confidence intervals provide much more information and are preferred when making inferences.

00:44.360 --> 00:47.030
